---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../../components/CTA.astro';

const pageDescription = "Restore ocular alignment and binocular vision with specialized squint (strabismus) treatment for adults and children by AIIMS-trained Dr. Rajeswari.";
---

<MainLayout title="Squint & Strabismus Treatment in Chennai" description={pageDescription}>  <!-- Service Header -->
  <section class="bg-blue-900 text-white py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="md:w-1/2">
        <span class="text-blue-300 font-bold tracking-wider uppercase text-sm mb-4 block">Ocular Alignment</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-6 leading-tight">Squint & Strabismus Treatment</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Expert evaluation and treatment for eye alignment issues in both children and adults to restore binocular vision and confidence.
        </p>
        <a href="#book" class="bg-white text-blue-900 font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-md shadow-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition inline-block">Consult Dr. Rajeswari</a>
      </div>
      <div class="md:w-1/2 w-full">
        <img src="/images/squint.jpg" alt="Corrective eye alignment and symmetry evaluation" class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl border-4 border-white/10 w-full object-cover aspect-video" onerror="this.src='https://placehold.co/800x500/1e3a8a/ffffff?text=Alignment+Evaluation'"/>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-blue max-w-none text-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-6">Understanding Squint (Strabismus)</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        A squint, medically known as strabismus, is a condition where the eyes do not look in exactly the same direction at the same time. While one eye looks straight ahead, the other eye may turn inward, outward, upward, or downward. 
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-900 mt-12 mb-6">Pediatric Squint & "Lazy Eye"</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        When a child develops a squint, the brain may begin to ignore the image from the turned eye to prevent double vision. If left untreated, this can lead to Amblyopia, commonly known as "lazy eye," causing permanent visual impairment. <strong>Early intervention is crucial. A squint will not simply "correct itself" as a child grows.</strong>
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-8 rounded-xl border border-blue-100 my-10">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">Treatment Pathways</h3>
        <p class="mb-4 text-slate-700 font-medium">Depending on the specific type and severity of the strabismus, treatment may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 font-medium">
          <li><strong>Prescription Glasses:</strong> Often the first step, specifically for refractive squints.</li>
          <li><strong>Patching Therapy:</strong> Covering the stronger eye to force the brain to use and strengthen the "lazy" eye.</li>
          <li><strong>Eye Exercises (Orthoptics):</strong> To improve eye coordination and focus.</li>
          <li><strong>Surgical Correction:</strong> A highly precise day-care procedure to adjust the tension of the eye muscles and restore proper alignment.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-900 mt-12 mb-6">Adult Squint Correction</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Adults can develop squints due to medical conditions (like diabetes or thyroid disease), trauma, or untreated childhood strabismus. Adult squint surgery is highly effective, not just for cosmetic reasons, but to eliminate double vision and alleviate severe eye strain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA 
    title="Book a Strabismus Evaluation"
    address="39/2, R K Shanmugam Salai, K K Nagar, Chennai – 600078"
    phone="+91 63813 02828"
  />
</MainLayout>
